 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What voltage battery do heated jackets use?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Most heated jackets and vests use 7.4V DC batteries. This provides optimal heat output while keeping the battery compact and safe for wearable use. Some lower-power heated accessories like pillows use 5V USB output instead.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the MOQ for heating battery OEM?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">MOQ starts at 500 units for standard OEM models with custom logo. Custom ODM with new connector types or capacity tuning: 1,000-2,000 units. Sample turnaround: 3-7 days for standard, 10-15 days for custom.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can you match our existing heated jacket connector?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">▼</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. WOWOHCOOL supports custom connector matching including DC barrel connectors (3.5mm, 5.5mm), magnetic pogo pins, and proprietary connectors. Send us your existing battery or connector sample and we'll match it exactly.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What is the operating temperature range?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">WOWOHCOOL heating batteries operate from -20°C to 60°C, making them suitable for extreme cold weather heated apparel applications. Discharge performance is optimized for low-temperature environments where standard Li-ion cells lose 30-50% capacity.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">How long does a 7.4V 5000mAh heated jacket battery last?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">A 7.4V 5000mAh battery provides 37Wh of energy. On a typical 3-zone heated jacket: approximately 7.4 hours on low (5W), 4.6 hours on medium (8W), or 3.1 hours on high heat (12W). Actual runtime varies by heating zone count, ambient temperature, and garment insulation.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">Can heated jacket batteries be taken on airplanes?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Yes. All WOWOHCOOL heating batteries are under 100Wh (the largest 14400mAh model is approximately 106Wh at maximum — we can configure capacity to stay within the 100Wh IATA carry-on limit). UN38.3 certified with full MSDS documentation for airline compliance. Batteries under 100Wh are permitted in carry-on luggage without pre-approval.</p>
 </details>
 <details class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-200 group">
 <summary class="font-black text-slate-900 cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center text-sm uppercase">What certifications do heated clothing batteries need for Amazon?<span class="text-brandOrange group-open:rotate-180 transition">&#9660;</span></summary>
 <p class="faq-answer text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-4">Amazon US requires UL certification (UL 2054 or UL 1642) for lithium batteries sold on their platform. Additionally, UN38.3 is needed for shipping, and FCC for the product listing. WOWOHCOOL provides CE/FCC/RoHS as standard and assists with UL certification application and testing coordination.</p>
 </details>
